1
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:09,860
{\pos(194,190)\fs30\fad(400,400)}细 细 的 红 线

2
00:01:58,510 --> 00:02:01,390
世上为何有这么多战争?
{\ren}What's this war in the heart of nature?

3
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:07,480
万物为何自相残杀?
{\ren}Why does nature vie with itself?

4
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:11,270
陆地和海洋为何互相对抗?
{\ren}The land contend with the sea?

5
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:25,410
大自然是否充满仇恨?
{\ren}Is there an avenging power in nature?

6
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,790
善恶是否同时存在?
{\ren}Not one power, but two?

7
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:25,160
我记得我母亲临终前
{\ren}I remember my mother when she was dying.

8
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,580
脸色苍白 形如槁木
{\ren}Looked all shrunk up and grey.

9
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:35,040
我问她害不害怕?
{\ren}I asked her if she was afraid.

10
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:38,840
她只是摇摇头
{\ren}She just shook her head.

11
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:43,050
我不敢面对她的死亡
{\ren}I was afraid to touch the death seen in her.

12
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:49,800
也不觉得她蒙主荣召是一件好事
{\ren}I couldn't find nothing beautiful or up lifting about her going back to God.

13
00:04:52,930 --> 00:04:57,240
听说精神能永垂不朽 不过我没见过
{\ren}I heard people talk about immortality, but I ain't seen it.

14
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:08,130
不知道我死时会怎样
{\ren}I wondered how it'd be when I died.

15
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:15,180
当你知道那是最后一口气不知道是什么感觉
{\ren}What it'd be like to know that this breath now was the last one you was ever gonna draw.

16
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,650
我希望能和她一样坦然面对
{\ren}I just hope I can meet it the same way she did.

17
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:26,440
跟她一样...平静
{\ren}With the same... calm.

18
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:34,120
当心灵得到平静 精神就能永垂不朽
{\ren}Cos that's where it's hidden - the immortality I hadn't seen.

19
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:17,870
这里的小孩不会打架
{\ren}Kids around here never fight.

20
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:20,410
有时候会
{\ren}Sometimes.

21
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:23,500
他们在玩耍的时候
{\ren}Sometimes when you see them playing

22
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:25,750
总是会打架
{\ren}they always fight!

23
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:32,220
- 他怕我吗? - 有一点
{\ren}- Is she afraid of me? - Little bit.

24
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,970
- 你怕我吗? - 怕
{\ren}- Are you afraid of me? - Yes.

25
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:40,180
- 为什么? - 因为你看起来...
{\ren}- Why? - Cos you look...

26
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,600
...像是个军人
{\ren}You look as an army!

27
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:45,770
- 我像军人? - 对
{\ren}- I look army? - Yes.

28
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,610
无所谓
{\ren}Well, that don't matter.

29
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,410
这不重要
{\ren}It doesn't matter.

30
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:58,950
- 孩子累了 - 对
{\ren}- Baby's tired. - Yes.

31
00:08:00,410 --> 00:08:03,000
他游累了就会睡
{\ren}If she swims, she wants, she will sleep.

32
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:34,900
好 来
{\ren}All right, come on. Turn around.

33
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:37,070
快...快...快
{\ren}Go, go, go, go. Go!

34
00:08:37,910 --> 00:08:39,990
快点...快点...
{\ren}Come on, go.

35
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:46,000
快 快 快
{\ren}Go, go, go, go!

36
00:10:23,260 --> 00:10:27,680
威特 是美军的巡逻艇
{\ren}Witt, patrol boat!She's American.

37
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,660
它怎么会单独出现?
{\ren}What's it doing out here all alone?

38
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:10,480
威特 你一点都没变
{\ren}You haven't changed at all, have you, Witt?

39
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,850
什么也没学到
{\ren}You haven't learned a thing.

40
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:19,190
当别人信任你你就肯为他赴汤蹈火
{\ren}All a man has to do is leave it to you, you'll put your head in the noose for him.

41
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:27,660
你逃过几年兵?
{\ren}How many times you been AWOL?

42
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,370
你当兵六年了
{\ren}Been in the army, what? Six years now?

43
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:37,460
如果要学聪明
{\ren}Ain't it time you smartened up and stopped being such a punk recruit?

44
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,630
现在该是时候了
{\ren}I mean, if you're ever gonna.

45
00:11:39,710 --> 00:11:41,800
我们不能都当聪明人
{\ren}We can't all be smart.

46
00:11:43,380 --> 00:11:45,890
没错 真可惜
{\ren}No, we can't, and that's a shame.

47
00:11:45,970 --> 00:11:48,060
看看你
{\ren}Look at you.

48
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:57,020
你在我的连队不能乖乖服役
{\ren}Truth is, you can't take straight duty in my company.

49
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:01,990
你在这世上不能成为 一个好的军人
{\ren}You'll never be a real soldier, not in God's world.

50
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:08,370
这是C连 我是副连长
{\ren}This is C Company, of which I'm First Sergeant. I run this outfit.

51
00:12:08,450 --> 00:12:13,290
史塔洛上尉是连长 这里是我话事 任何人都不可以违抗
{\ren}Captain Staros, he's the CO, but I'm the guy who runs it. Nobody's gonna foul that up.

52
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:17,210
你只是一张吃饭的嘴
{\ren}You're just another mouth for me to feed.

53
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,590
你本来要接受军事审判
{\ren}Normally, you'd be court-martialled.

54
00:12:23,090 --> 00:12:25,180
算你好运
{\ren}But I worked a deal for ya.

55
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:27,350
我给你另作安排
{\ren}Gotta consider yourself lucky.

56
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:32,640
我派你到纪律部队
{\ren}I'm sending you to a disciplinary outfit.

57
00:12:32,730 --> 00:12:37,150
当担架兵 照顾伤兵
{\ren}You'll be a stretcher-bearer. You'll be taking care of the wounded.

58
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:41,440
我能接受任何处罚
{\ren}I can take anything you dish out.

59
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:43,860
我一个人就比你好两倍
{\ren}I'm twice the man you are.

60
00:12:55,330 --> 00:12:57,420
在这个世界里
{\ren}In this world...

61
00:12:58,330 --> 00:13:02,170
一个人根本微不足道
{\ren}a man himself is nothing.

62
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:09,890
只有这一个世界
{\ren}And there ain't no world but this one.

63
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,680
你错了 副连长
{\ren}You're wrong there, Top.

64
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,560
我见过另一个世界
{\ren}I seen another world.

65
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:29,030
有时候我觉得这只是我的想像
{\ren}Sometimes I think it was just... my imagination.

66
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:33,540
好
{\ren}Well,

67
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:36,330
我和你的看法不同
{\ren}then you've seen things I never will.

68
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:51,510
这个世界在自我毁灭
{\ren}We're living in a world that's blowing itself to hell as fast as everybody can arrange it.

69
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:57,440
你只以只眼开只眼闭
{\ren}In a situation like that all a man can do is shut his eyes and let nothing touch him.

70
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,600
为自己着想
{\ren}Look out for himself.

71
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:14,580
我可能是你最好的朋友
{\ren}I might be the best friend you ever had.

72
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,870
你自己都不知道
{\ren}You don't even know it.

73
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:52,740
他憎死你了
{\ren}He hates you worse than poison.

74
00:14:57,540 --> 00:15:01,000
我不觉得他憎我 因为我不憎他
{\ren}I never felt he hated me, cos I don't hate him.

75
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,040
我爱C队的兄弟
{\ren}I love Charlie Company.

76
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:51,090
他们是我的家人
{\ren}They're my people.

77
00:16:15,990 --> 00:16:17,870
这个岛叫"顽石"
{\ren}They call it "The Rock".

78
00:16:17,950 --> 00:16:21,200
原本无人占领 后来让日军盖了机场
{\ren}Nobody wants this island. Japs just put an airfield there.

79
00:16:21,290 --> 00:16:23,160
主要战区在这里
{\ren}Fighting's confined to this area.

80
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:28,840
这是攻击澳洲的途径亦是进攻美国的海道
{\ren}This is their road to Australia, and this is their way of controlling the sea lanes to America.

81
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:34,130
若要阻止日军攻占南太平洋 就得在这里开战
{\ren}If we're gonna stop the Japs' advance into the South Pacific, we've gotta do it right there.

82
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:38,720
海军陆战队已经试过 现在轮到我们
{\ren}The Marines have done their job. Now it's our turn.

83
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:42,270
我们将奋不顾身
{\ren}Worked my ass off.

84
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:45,900
尽量迎合将军
{\ren}Brown-nosed the generals.

85
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:50,230
降低身份
{\ren}Degraded myself

86
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:55,280
为他们 为我家人
{\ren}for them and my family.

87
00:16:56,570 --> 00:16:58,660
和我的家
{\ren}For my home.

88
00:16:59,330 --> 00:17:02,620
- 我很敬佩你 上校 - 谢谢你 长官
{\ren}- I admire you, Colonel. I do. - Thank you, sir.

89
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:05,670
你这年纪的军官早已退休了
{\ren}Most men your age would have retired by now.

90
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:07,830
你是好军人
{\ren}It's OK.

91
00:17:08,540 --> 00:17:12,550
部队需要你这种成熟的长官
{\ren}We need general officers with maturity and character like you.

92
00:17:12,630 --> 00:17:16,010
我们有好的中士和中校
{\ren}We've got good sergeants and good lieutenant colonels.

93
00:17:16,090 --> 00:17:19,470
他们一当了上校 就想做将军
{\ren}But once a man gets those eagles, he can't wait to get that star.

94
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:21,640
于是成为政客
{\ren}He becomes a politician, right?

95
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,810
只会拍上司的马屁
{\ren}Goes along to get along.

96
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:28,520
很难坚持原则
{\ren}So goddamn hard to stay upright.

97
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:32,650
- 你说得对 长官 - 上将会注意我的表现
{\ren}- You said it there, sir. - With the Admiral watching, which he will be.

98
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:35,650
- 一定有人盯着你 - 嗯
{\ren}- There's always someone watching. - Yeah.

99
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:38,700
像只猎鹰
{\ren}Like a hawk.

100
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:41,950
总是有人想抢你的功劳
{\ren}Always someone ready to jump in, if you're not.

101
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,380
- 你有儿子吗 上校? - 有的 长官
{\ren}- D'you have a son, Colonel? - Yes, sir.

102
00:17:56,470 --> 00:18:00,890
很好 不能让子孙打这场烂仗
{\ren}Good. We don't want our sons or grandsons fighting this war 30 years from now, do we?

103
00:18:00,970 --> 00:18:04,520
- 没错 是不能 - 那就全力攻敌
{\ren}- No, sir, we sure don't. - Then you crush 'em without mercy.

104
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:07,640
把敌人赶尽杀绝 抢下机场
{\ren}You dig them out of the hills and protect that airfield.

105
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:09,600
是的 长官
{\ren}Yes, sir.

106
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:15,860
你有没有想过日军为何在这儿盖机场?
{\ren}You wonder why... Why did the Japs put an airfield there of all places?

107
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:20,030
我们对大局不太清楚
{\ren}I guess we don't know the bigger picture, if there is such a thing.

108
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:24,200
- 你认为呢? - 我从不想这种问题
{\ren}- What do you think? - Well, sir, I never ask myself that question.

109
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:25,950
你很谦虚
{\ren}You're a humble man.

110
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:31,290
没人要这座岛...除了你
{\ren}Nobody wants that island... but you.

111
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:34,880
你有多大的决心?
{\ren}How much do you want it?

112
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,380
我会全力以赴
{\ren}As much as I have to, sir.

113
00:18:40,630 --> 00:18:43,300
家人为我做的牺牲
{\ren}All they sacrificed for me

114
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:49,100
就像覆水难收
{\ren}poured out like water on the ground.

115
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,820
我本来能好好爱他们
{\ren}All I might have given for love's sake.

116
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:14,420
太迟了
{\ren}Too late.

117
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:21,340
我的心已死
{\ren}Died...

118
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,850
像树木一样慢慢凋零
{\ren}slow as a tree.

119
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:29,180
你感觉得到吗?
{\ren}D'you feel it?

120
00:19:29,890 --> 00:19:31,980
是的 长官
{\ren}Yes, sir.

121
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:38,190
谢谢你 长官
{\ren}Thank you, sir.

122
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:03,180
权力越大 恐惧越深
{\ren}The closer you are to Caesar, the greater the fear.

123
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:23,490
我就是感到害怕
{\ren}I just can't help how damn scared I am, sarge, all right?

124
00:20:24,530 --> 00:20:26,200
无法控制
{\ren}I can't help it. I got...

125
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:29,660
小时候我继父常用砖块打我
{\ren}My stepdaddy took a block and beat me when I was real little

126
00:20:29,740 --> 00:20:32,540
我好怕 老是躲起来
{\ren}and I was scared and I used to run, I used to hide.

127
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:36,290
时常睡在鸡窝
{\ren}Hell, I slept in the chicken coop a whole lot of nights.

128
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:40,550
我以为我不会再害怕
{\ren}And I never thought it'd get no worse than that.

129
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:45,680
但是现在我分秒都在害怕
{\ren}But I'm living by the... by the minute here. I'm counting the seconds.

130
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:50,220
马上就要登陆一定会遭到空袭
{\ren}Hell, we're gonna be landing soon and there's gonna be air raids.

131
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:53,770
我们会阵亡在滩头
{\ren}We're probably gonna die before we get off the beach.

132
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:57,860
这艘船就像漂流的坟墓
{\ren}This place is... It's like a big floating graveyard.

133
00:20:57,940 --> 00:21:02,150
- 你叫什么 小子? - 我退伍后想买一辆车
{\ren}- What's your name, kid? - I wanna own an automobile when I get out.

134
00:21:03,610 --> 00:21:06,410
- 你叫什么? - 爱德华崔恩
{\ren}- What's your name? - Edward, Edward B Train.

135
00:21:06,490 --> 00:21:07,570
崔恩?
{\ren}Train?

136
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:13,080
只有上帝和死亡是永恒的
{\ren}The only things that are permanent is, is dying and the Lord. That's it.

137
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:19,080
我只担心这些 这场战争不是你我的终点
{\ren}That's all you gotta worry about. This war ain't... gonna be the end of me or you neither.

138
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:22,500
- 会遇到空袭吗? - 我怎么知道?
{\ren}- Think we'll catch an air raid? - How in the hell should I know?

139
00:21:22,590 --> 00:21:27,340
别的大兵说上次进攻就没有
{\ren}All's I know are them crew guys said they didn't catch no air raid the last time.

140
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:31,010
上上一次他们差点被炸死
{\ren}On the other hand, time before last they nearly got blew up.

141
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,970
你要我怎么说
{\ren}What d'you want me to tell you?

142
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:36,100
多谢了 你什么也没说
{\ren}You're a big help, Tills. Nothing. Tell me nothing.

143
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:37,650
不过我要告诉你
{\ren}Tell you something.

144
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:42,320
我们在船上就像是死鸭子
{\ren}We're sitting out here on this ocean like a couple of fuckin' ducks in these boats.

145
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,360
我早就知道
{\ren}I already know that.

146
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,200
好好想一想 提奥
{\ren}Well, brood on it, Tills.

147
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,570
好好地想
{\ren}Brood on it.

148
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:52,080
- 不看好戏吗? - 没兴趣
{\ren}- Ain't you watching the fun? - I ain't interested.

149
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:56,620
- 太迫了 - 就算不迫我也不想看
{\ren}- Yeah, I guess it is pretty crowded. - Wouldn't be interested, even if it wasn't.

150
00:21:56,710 --> 00:21:59,500
我要去拿那把手枪
{\ren}Well, I'm on my way to get me that pistol.

151
00:21:59,580 --> 00:22:01,250
是吗? 开心点
{\ren}Yeah? Well, have fun.

152
00:22:01,340 --> 00:22:03,550
是啊 开心点
{\ren}Yeah, have fun.

153
00:22:03,630 --> 00:22:08,470
有手枪才能对付日本武士刀
{\ren}You'll wish you had one once we get ashore and run into some of them samurai sabres.

154
00:22:08,550 --> 00:22:12,180
快开门 给我开门...
{\ren}Open this door! Open this goddamn door!

155
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:14,140
快开门
{\ren}Open the door!

156
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:39,750
我入伍时没想到会有这下场
{\ren}I never bargained for nothing like this when I signed up for this man's army before the war.

157
00:22:39,830 --> 00:22:44,630
我怎么知道会打仗? 你倒是说说
{\ren}How was I supposed to know there was gonna be a fuckin' war, huh? Answer me that.

158
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:51,590
我只知道C连最衰了
{\ren}All I know is Charlie Company's always getting screwed. Always.

159
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,430
我也知道是谁的错
{\ren}And I can tell you whose fault it is, too.

160
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:56,470
就是我们的连长
{\ren}It's that captain of ours.

161
00:22:56,560 --> 00:23:01,350
他害大家被派上这艘鬼船
{\ren}First he gets us stuck off on this boat where we don't know a fucking soul.

162
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:06,900
而且是第四批登陆部队
{\ren}Then he gets us stuck way down in fourth place on the list to get off this son of a bitch.

163
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:22,670
连长 你好
{\ren}Hello, Captain.

164
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:10,380
档案说你在战前是军官
{\ren}I read in your 201 file that you were an officer before the war.

165
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:13,130
怎么会变成二等兵?
{\ren}How'd you end up a private?

166
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:15,300
因为我太太
{\ren}Cos of my wife.

167
00:24:16,050 --> 00:24:18,260
我本来在工兵部队
{\ren}I was in the corps of engineers.

168
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:22,520
我和她从来没分开过
{\ren}We'd never been separated before,

169
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,690
连一晚都没有
{\ren}not even for a night.

170
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:29,530
我忍受了四个月最后终于放弃
{\ren}I took it for four months and then I quit.

171
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,530
辞职不干
{\ren}Just resigned.

172
00:24:34,490 --> 00:24:37,240
我被送回美国
{\ren}They sent me back to the States.

173
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:40,410
永远不能当军官
{\ren}They told me I'd never get another commission.

174
00:24:40,490 --> 00:24:46,170
他们说要徵召我入伍让我当步兵
{\ren}They said they'd see to it I got drafted and that I for damn sure'd be in the infantry.

175
00:24:46,790 --> 00:24:48,880
那些浑蛋
{\ren}Sons of bitches.

176
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:51,590
我不怪他们
{\ren}No, I don't blame them.

177
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:56,090
她在哪里?
{\ren}Well, where is she now?

178
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:59,050
在家里
{\ren}She's home.

179
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:14,860
我并不怕死
{\ren}Why should i be afraid to die?

180
00:25:17,490 --> 00:25:18,950
因为我已属于你
{\ren}I belong to you.

181
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:24,040
快...快...快...
{\ren}Move! Move! Move!

182
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:26,210
快 快
{\ren}Move! Move!

183
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:34,590
快点...
{\ren}Move! Move!

184
00:25:34,670 --> 00:25:35,920
快 快
{\ren}Moving out!

185
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:40,180
如果我先走 我会等你的
{\ren}If i go first, I'll wait for you there.

186
00:25:41,510 --> 00:25:43,930
就在死亡的另一边
{\ren}On the otherside of the dark waters.

187
00:25:51,230 --> 00:25:53,320
贝尔 戴上头盔
{\ren}Put your helmet on.

188
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:56,530
你与我同在
{\ren}Be with me now.

189
00:26:06,580 --> 00:26:09,080
- 压力很大 对吧? - 是的 长官
{\ren}- Feeling the pressure, Captain? - Yes, sir.

190
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:12,750
我喜欢你 上尉
{\ren}I like you, Captain.

191
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:18,340
我要你知道我很支持你
{\ren}And I just want you to know, well, we're in this thing together. All right?

192
00:26:18,430 --> 00:26:22,510
你先逼近敌区 我会赶上来
{\ren}Keep pressing inland till you reach the line. I'll catch up with you there.

193
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,470
- 是的 长官 - 由你全权指挥
{\ren}- Yes, sir. - It's all yours, Captain.

194
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:27,020
让开 让开
{\ren}Gangway! Gangway there!

195
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,560
我要过去
{\ren}Coming through!

196
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:31,560
班长马上报到
{\ren}Squad leaders! Both teams!

197
00:26:31,650 --> 00:26:33,980
在这里
{\ren}This way, son. This way, right here.

198
00:26:35,030 --> 00:26:37,110
准备上登陆船
{\ren}Stand by to go over the side!

199
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:51,920
我们在天上的父
{\ren}Our Father, who art in heaven...

200
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:56,800
免我们的债如同我们免人的债
{\ren}And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors.

201
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,510
国度权柄荣耀全是您的 阿们
{\ren}For Thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory.

202
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,280
你们很幸运
{\ren}Your outfit's lucky.

203
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,450
运输船刚被日军发现
{\ren}Transports must've been spotted.

204
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:20,450
幸好你们下来了
{\ren}You're getting outta here just ahead of time.

205
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:33,340
深呼吸 你得深呼吸
{\ren}Take a breath, mister. You gotta breathe!

206
00:29:03,490 --> 00:29:05,160
- 这是C连吗? - 是的
{\ren}- You Charlie Company? - Yeah.

207
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:07,330
我们深入内陆一英里 什么也没有
{\ren}We went in a mile. Nothing there.

208
00:29:07,410 --> 00:29:09,960
一个礼拜都没动静
{\ren}Some oil drums. There'd be nothing there for...

209
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,420
- 一个礼拜 - 一个礼拜 长官
{\ren}- A week. - A week, sir.

210
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:13,960
无人伤亡 日军大概都跑了
{\ren}No casualties. Japs must've hauled ass.

211
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:17,090
我们受迫击炮攻击 无人伤亡
{\ren}Two mortars hit the beach, but most guys came in standing up.

212
00:29:17,170 --> 00:29:19,050
这地方很不可思议
{\ren}Darnedest thing I ever did see.

213
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:24,100
还有鱼住在树上
{\ren}They got fish that live in trees.

214
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:32,270
指挥部好像没搞清楚状况
{\ren}If they didn't know this beach was deserted, what else don't they know?

215
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:07,280
您化身为宇宙万物
{\ren}Who are you to live in all these many forms?

216
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:41,780
万物皆难逃一死
{\ren}Your death that captures all.

217
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:52,120
您也是生命的泉源
{\ren}You, too, are the source of all that's gonna be born.

218
00:32:16,270 --> 00:32:18,350
您充满荣耀
{\ren}Your glory.

219
00:32:21,650 --> 00:32:23,730
慈悲
{\ren}Mercy.

220
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:27,360
宁静
{\ren}Peace.

221
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:31,410
真理
{\ren}Truth.

222
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,330
您能安抚人心
{\ren}You give calm a spirit,

223
00:32:43,380 --> 00:32:45,460
给人们谅解
{\ren}understanding,

224
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:49,340
和勇气
{\ren}courage.

225
00:32:54,010 --> 00:32:56,100
使人得到满足
{\ren}The contented heart.

226
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:38,490
医务兵 这里
{\ren}Get a medic here!

227
00:36:43,740 --> 00:36:48,290
也许每个人都有共同的灵魂 和相同的命运
{\ren}Maybe all men got one big soul who everybody's a part of.

228
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,500
每张脸孔都是同一个人
{\ren}All faces of the same man.

229
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:56,840
一个大我
{\ren}One big self.

230
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:34,170
每个人都想获得救赎
{\ren}Everyone looking for salvation by himself.

231
00:37:41,010 --> 00:37:45,510
像炭火般燃烧生命
{\ren}Each like a coal drawn from the fire.

232
00:38:17,550 --> 00:38:20,380
我们要攻上那座山头
{\ren}We're going straight up that hill there.

233
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:28,140
- 办不到 上校 - 我们无法包抄敌军
{\ren}- We can't do that, Colonel. - Well, there's no way to outflank it.

234
00:38:28,220 --> 00:38:31,140
左边的悬崖底下是河流
{\ren}On the left is a cliff that falls down into the river.

235
00:38:31,230 --> 00:38:35,020
日军守住丛林 我们得正面突袭
{\ren}The Japanese hold the jungle. It has to be taken frontally.

236
00:38:37,230 --> 00:38:40,150
食水怎么办? 山上没清水
{\ren}What about water, sir? It's not getting up here.

237
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:42,650
我的兄弟都因为脱水昏倒
{\ren}My men are... passing out, sir.

238
00:38:49,970 --> 00:38:54,330
他们能发牢骚就能打仗
{\ren}Only time you worry about a soldier is when he stops bitching.

239
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:11,850
并肩前进 第三排留守
{\ren}We're all gonna attack abreast. Third Platoon in reserve.

240
00:39:11,930 --> 00:39:15,310
我们得越过三个山丘
{\ren}We've gotta cross those three folds of ground. You see?

241
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,190
然后再攻下山头
{\ren}Once we get beyond that, we gotta attack that hill.

242
00:39:28,990 --> 00:39:35,040
上校说不能采取包抄攻势 我们得正面突袭
{\ren}Colonel says there's no way to outflank it, so we gotta take it head-on by frontal assault.

243
00:39:36,790 --> 00:39:38,250
- 伟特 - 是
{\ren}- Whyte? - Yeah?

244
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:41,340
- 看到山坡前面吗? - 看到了
{\ren}- See the grassy ridges at the foot of that hill? - Yeah.

245
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:46,430
等你攻上山坡 找到敌军据点然后消灭他们
{\ren}When you get to the end of that field, eliminate all strong points on those ridges.

246
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:54,730
那儿一定有敌军守住
{\ren}I'm sure the Japs got something there to protect the approaches.

247
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:49,920
主啊 您在吗?
{\ren}Are you here?

248
00:41:04,230 --> 00:41:06,310
别让我背叛您
{\ren}Let me not betray you.

249
00:41:10,020 --> 00:41:12,110
别让我背叛我的兄弟
{\ren}Let me not betray my men.

250
00:41:19,780 --> 00:41:22,080
您让我充满信心 和希望
{\ren}In you I place my trust.

251
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:37,180
(希腊语)

252
00:41:38,090 --> 00:41:40,180
玫瑰般的黎明
{\ren}Rosy-fingered dawn.

253
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:44,100
你是希腊人
{\ren}You're Greek, aren't you, Captain?

254
00:41:44,180 --> 00:41:46,270
读过荷马的史诗吗?
{\ren}D'you ever read Homer?

255
00:41:46,350 --> 00:41:50,860
我在西点军校读过希腊原文
{\ren}We read Homer at the Point.In Greek.

256
00:41:50,940 --> 00:41:54,440
有多少炮兵支援火力?
{\ren}What kind of artillery support do we have, sir? Over.

257
00:41:54,530 --> 00:41:59,110
- 两组105榴弹炮 - 一点都没有用
{\ren}- Two batteries of 105s. - They won't make a dent. Over.

258
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:03,580
不过能提高士气 日军会被炸得很难看
{\ren}No, but it bucks the men up. It'll look like the Japs are catching hell.

259
00:42:57,420 --> 00:42:59,300
兄弟们
{\ren}OK, you guys.

260
00:42:59,380 --> 00:43:01,050
准备上吧
{\ren}This is it.

261
00:43:01,140 --> 00:43:03,640
每组十人攻上山头
{\ren}We're going down in groups often.

262
00:43:05,060 --> 00:43:09,520
快速前进才不会成为目标
{\ren}There's no point in going by rushes. Only make a better target stopped, so...

263
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,940
一路跑上去
{\ren}run all the way.

264
00:43:12,020 --> 00:43:15,360
我们被选上 别无选择 非去不可
{\ren}We ain't got no choice. We're picked, so we gotta go.

265
00:43:18,490 --> 00:43:20,780
我亲自带领先锋队
{\ren}I'm gonna take the first bunch myself.

266
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:23,200
我要戴尔跟着我 戴尔?
{\ren}I want Charlie Dale with me. Dale?

267
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:25,990
叫兄弟在山坡集合
{\ren}You go organise them guys that's up there.

268
00:43:31,710 --> 00:43:34,000
五分钟后出发
{\ren}Moving out in five minutes.

269
00:43:34,880 --> 00:43:36,500
走吧
{\ren}Let's go.

270
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:42,590
施高?
{\ren}Sico?

271
00:43:43,390 --> 00:43:46,350
- 你怎么了? - 我的肚子好痛
{\ren}- What's wrong with you? - I'm sick to my stomach.

272
00:43:46,430 --> 00:43:49,770
起来 小心我踢扁你
{\ren}Sico, you get up now, or I'll kick you so hard you're gonna be sick.

273
00:43:49,850 --> 00:43:51,640
我站不起来
{\ren}I can't. I would if I could.

274
00:43:51,730 --> 00:43:54,060
我生病了
{\ren}I'm sick.

275
00:43:54,150 --> 00:43:56,020
我病了
{\ren}I'm sick.

276
00:43:56,110 --> 00:43:58,190
你没有病 起来
{\ren}You ain't sick. Get up!

277
00:44:02,490 --> 00:44:05,910
- 施高 怎么了? - 不晓得
{\ren}- What's the matter, Sico? - I don't know, Sergeant.

278
00:44:05,990 --> 00:44:09,160
肚子好痛 好像是胃痉孪
{\ren}It's my stomach. I'm in pain, I got cramps.

279
00:44:09,240 --> 00:44:11,500
我病了 坐不起来
{\ren}I can't even sit up straight. I'm sick.

280
00:44:15,500 --> 00:44:17,380
- 给我起来! - 别逼他了
{\ren}- Come on, get up! - Leave him.

281
00:44:17,460 --> 00:44:21,720
谁要替我拿步枪? 我带你找医官
{\ren}I need a volunteer to carry the BAR! Drop your gear. I'm taking you to the medics.

282
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:23,880
谢谢你 副连长
{\ren}Thank you, Sergeant.

283
00:44:26,180 --> 00:44:28,260
别跟我争
{\ren}Don't argue with me.

284
00:44:28,350 --> 00:44:30,430
祝好运 杰克
{\ren}Good luck, Keck.

285
00:45:57,320 --> 00:45:59,410
也许他们撤退了
{\ren}Maybe they pulled out.

286
00:48:10,160 --> 00:48:11,790
快趴下!
{\ren}Hit dirt!

287
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:14,120
趴下来!
{\ren}Hit dirt!

288
00:48:19,210 --> 00:48:21,960
冷静点...冷静点...
{\ren}Calm down, calm down, calm down, calm down.

289
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:28,800
担架兵
{\ren}Stretcher-bearers!

290
00:48:44,490 --> 00:48:46,150
这儿
{\ren}Come on!

291
00:48:46,240 --> 00:48:48,320
担架兵 在这儿
{\ren}Stretcher-bearers, this way!

292
00:48:49,410 --> 00:48:52,620
- 去救那兄弟 - 已经有八 九名伤兵...
{\ren}- Go get that man. - We already got eight or nine down there...

293
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:56,750
- 别跟我争 我要救他 - 管不了他们了
{\ren}- Don't argue with me! Get that man! - He's not the one we should think about...

294
00:48:56,830 --> 00:49:00,130
该死 全都要救 我是指挥官
{\ren}Goddamn it, all of you! Am I in command here or am I not?!

295
00:49:00,210 --> 00:49:04,300
- 难道你是连长吗? - 我只是说别人伤得更重
{\ren}- Am I the captain or a goddamn private? - Others are hit bad. That's all I meant.

296
00:49:06,260 --> 00:49:08,390
- 二兵 听我的命令 - 是 长官!
{\ren}- I gave you an order, private! - Yes, sir!

297
00:49:11,140 --> 00:49:12,810
你好 副连长
{\ren}Hello, First Sergeant.

298
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:16,980
我们要救谁?
{\ren}Who we going after over here?

299
00:49:17,770 --> 00:49:19,860
应该是积克
{\ren}We think it's Jacques.

300
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:22,070
积克老兄
{\ren}Ol' Jockey.

301
00:49:22,150 --> 00:49:24,860
真是倒霉
{\ren}Well, shit. That's, that's, that's too bad.

302
00:49:25,360 --> 00:49:26,820
长官?
{\ren}Sir?

303
00:49:27,490 --> 00:49:32,780
把积克抬回去我能回来吗?
{\ren}Sir? Sir, can I come back to the company after we get Jockey back to the battalion?

304
00:49:33,620 --> 00:49:37,710
- 好 你要得到许可 - 当然 我的步枪
{\ren}- OK, but you gotta get permission. - Sure. And my rifle.

305
00:49:40,750 --> 00:49:43,170
力奇 你还活着
{\ren}Nicky! You're still alive!

306
00:49:44,090 --> 00:49:45,960
继续前进! 继续前进!
{\ren}Keep moving! Keep moving!

307
00:49:47,050 --> 00:49:53,060
太好了 史塔奥 好久没见到这么猛烈的攻击
{\ren}Magnificent, Staros, magnificent. The finest thing these old eyes have seen in a long time!

308
00:49:53,140 --> 00:49:57,640
你指挥得很好 我会请营长给你功勋
{\ren}Beautifully conceived and executed! You'll be mentioned in battalion orders.

309
00:49:57,730 --> 00:50:00,270
伟特排长的表现也很棒
{\ren}Young Whyte led beautifully.

310
00:50:00,350 --> 00:50:02,440
是 长官
{\ren}Yes, sir. Over.

311
00:50:02,560 --> 00:50:05,400
派第二排增援也很聪明
{\ren}But sending in your second too was brilliant.

312
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:10,990
就快攻上去了 伤亡不惨重 布兰也不错
{\ren}They may have carried the ridge. I don't think they were hurt too bad. Blane led well, too.

313
00:50:11,070 --> 00:50:13,870
他们发现多少据点?
{\ren}Now, how many emplacements did they locate?

314
00:50:13,950 --> 00:50:16,040
消灭了多少?
{\ren}Did they knock any out?

315
00:50:16,120 --> 00:50:20,170
中午就应该能攻上山头
{\ren}We ought to have those ridges cleaned out by noon! Over.

316
00:50:22,290 --> 00:50:24,590
史塔奥 你在吗?
{\ren}Hello! Hello! Staros, are you there?

317
00:50:24,670 --> 00:50:26,920
我在 长官
{\ren}Here, sir. Over.

318
00:50:27,010 --> 00:50:31,890
他们发现多少据点? 消灭了多少?
{\ren}I said, how many emplacements did they locate? Did they knock any out? Over.

319
00:50:31,970 --> 00:50:34,350
孩子们
{\ren}Children.

320
00:50:34,430 --> 00:50:37,270
我不知道
{\ren}I don't know, sir.

321
00:50:37,350 --> 00:50:41,850
什么意思? 你怎么会不知道?
{\ren}What the hell do you mean, you don't know? How can you not know? Over.

322
00:50:41,980 --> 00:50:46,270
我在第一座山丘后面
{\ren}I'm right here behind the first swell, sir. I'm right here behind the swell.

323
00:50:46,360 --> 00:50:48,690
要我站起来招手吗?
{\ren}You want me to stand up and wave? Over.

324
00:50:48,780 --> 00:50:51,990
我看到了 你得想办法
{\ren}No, I can see where you are. I want you to do something.

325
00:50:52,070 --> 00:50:55,280
快上去看看情况如何
{\ren}I want you to get up there and see what the situation is.

326
00:50:55,370 --> 00:50:57,620
今晚我就要你攻下山头
{\ren}I want Hill 210 in my hands tonight.

327
00:50:57,700 --> 00:51:01,040
上将一早就要来查看
{\ren}Now, goddamn it, the Admiral got up at dawn for this!

328
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:03,580
提起精神来 史塔奥
{\ren}Come to life up there, Staros. Out!

329
00:51:29,940 --> 00:51:32,030
上来
{\ren}Move up!

330
00:51:50,380 --> 00:51:51,840
嘿 杰克!
{\ren}Hey, Keck!

331
00:51:53,050 --> 00:51:54,930
干嘛?
